            <p>
Sumptuous 2021 action-adventure Kena: Bridge of Spirits is getting a sequel, despite previous word from its developer suggesting one was unlikely and it's coming to PlayStation 5 and PC later this year.
</p>
<p>
Kena: Scars of Kosmora, as the sequel is titled, sees developer Ember Lab returning to a world in which its titular protagonist is now a "more experienced" Spirit Guide. This time around, Kena is seeking answers to her lifelong affliction, and it's a journey that'll take her to the mysterious island of Kosmora, said to be "full of buried secrets from a tragic past".
</p>
<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Kena: Scars of Kosmora - Announce Trailer | PS5 Games" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/12EQpTwn4lY?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
