<h3>Project Windless</h3>
<p>Krafton's mysterious AAA project finally shows its face! Play as perhaps the henchest rooster of all time, as you slice through waves of enemies and take down gigantic monsters with two sharp swords and a red comb. No release date, as of yet.</p>
<h3>Galactic Racer story trailer</h3>
<p>Galactic Racer has a gameplay / story trailer, showing big crashes, exotic planets, and a few returning characters you may have spotted. It's coming out in 2026.</p>
<h3>007 First Light gets yet another trailer</h3>
<p>It's another James Bond trailer! More action, more wit, that classic guitar riff. A combination of gun play and hand-to-hand fighting gets a highlight too! It's out on the 27th May.</p>
<h3>Metal Gear Solid collection Volume 2</h3>
<p>Finally! Metal Gear Solid 4 is coming to modern platforms. Not just that, but Peace Walker (banger) is also included! It's out on the 27th August. The original MGS collection is also getting resolution upgrades, which you can toggle on at your pleasure.</p>
<h3>Darwin's Paradox</h3>
<p>Tactical Octopus Action. Tactical Octopus Action! Darwin's Paradox got a reveal trailer, but you can download a demo that includes an ode to Metal Gear Solid tomorrow</p>
<h3>Castlevania: Belmont's Curse</h3>
<p>It's a new 2D Castlevania! Set in France, Castlevania: Belmont's Curse is coming out in 2026. After a period porting classic Castlevania games to modern platforms, it's the first new 2D Castlevania in some time. </p>
<h3>Silent Hill Townfall</h3>
<p>A reveal trailer for a brand-new Silent Hill is here! Silent Hill Townfall is a first person horror game, with some lovely horrific hospitial equiment ickiness. It's out in 2026!</p>
<h3>Rev. Noir</h3>
<p>Another new game from Konmai, which is on something on a hot-streak this State of Play. Rev. Noir has no release date, but you can wishlist it now!</p>
<h3>John Wick reveal trailer</h3>
<p>A new John Wick game has been revealed! made by Sabre Interactive, you can wishlist it now. Now that's an exciting new reveal! Sadly, not much additional info, save for a few gameplay snippets.</p>
<h3>Marathon story / beta trailer</h3>
<p>Marathon got a new story / beta trailer. Not only did we get more gameplay footage and some tonal horror, but there's a Server Slam test happening between the 26th February to the 2nd March. It'll be available on PS5 and other platforms, so check it out! You can even unlock rewards for the full release. PlayStation Plus players can get unique charms that pay homage to other Sony big hitters.</p>
<h3>New games coming to PlayStation Plus</h3>
<p>Marvel's Spider-Man 2, Tekken: Dark Resurrection, Time Crisis, and Big Wank is coming to the PlayStation Plus catalogue and Classics collection. </p>
<h3>Saros trailer</h3>
<p>Saros got another gameplay trailer, showing off the "Come Back Stronger" feature. This ties to the Rogue-like elements of the game, in which you can permanently upgrade your armour and unlock perks. You can even impliment difficulty modifiers. The game is out on the 30th April, 2026.</p>

